Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
checkHierRoute(25.10)                                    checkHierRoute(25.10)

Name
       checkHierRoute  -  Checks  and reports hierarchy violations for nets in
       the specified partitions

Syntax
       checkHierRoute

       [-help]

       [-ptn {<ptnName> | <ptnList>}]

       [-outFile <outputFileName>]

       Checks and reports hierarchy violations for nets in the specified  par-
       titions.

       The following conditions for hierarchy violations are checked:

              * Intra-partition  nets: All routes of this net should be within
                the partition boundary.

              * Pure-Top nets: All routes of this net should  be  outside  the
                partition  boundary  or touch the partition boundary from out-
                side.

              * Inter-partition nets: At least one  route  of  this  net  must
                cross the partition boundary at partition pin. No route should
                cross the partition boundary at any other point.

       Note: You can use this command to check for hierarchy violations before
       you push down the signal routes with the partition -pushRoute command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each checkHierRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man checkHierRoute.

       -ptn {<ptnName> | <ptnList>}
              Report the nets that violate the hierarchy with respect  to  the
              specified partition(s).

              Default: The command checks the hierarchy violations for nets on
              all partitions.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -outFile <outputFileName>
              Prints the details of net-wise violations in the specified file.

              Default: By default, the name of the file is hier.rpt.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples of hierarchy violation conditions:
       The following are examples of hierarchy violation conditions:

              * If  wires of a inter-partition net, are crossing the partition
                boundary at a place other than the corresponding pin shape.

              * If wires of a inter-partition net, are crossing the  partition
                boundary at multiple places.

              * If wires of a pure top net, are crossing over a partition.

              * If wires of a intra partition net are going outside the bound-
                ary of its partition.

Example
       The  following command checks the violations for nets on all the parti-
       tions in the design. A report of  the  violations  is  printed  in  the
       hier.rpt file.

       checkHierRoute

       The output of this command on the display terminal is as follows:

